<h2>About</h2>
	<h3>Biography <a href="http://microformats.org/wiki/hcard" title="hCard enabled"><img src="images/icons/hcard.png" alt="(hCard enabled)"/></a></h3>
		<p><strong class="fn n"><span class="given-name">George</span> <span class="family-name">Watson</span></strong> (<abbr title="born" class="abbr">b.</abbr> <time class="bday" datetime="1994-06-23" title="1994-06-23">23 June 1994</time>), known pseudonymously as <span class="nickname">dendodge</span>, is a <span class="role">student</span> from <span class="adr"><span class="region">Lincolnshire</span>, in the <span class="country-name">United Kingdom</span></span>, currently studying for GCE A levels in mathematics and physics, and due to begin studying BSc Physics at university in <time class="dtstart" datetime="2013-09" title="2013-09">September 2013</time>.</p>
		<p>Between studying, he spends a lot of time on <a href="http://blog.dendodge.me" title="Tumblog" class="url ext">Tumblr</a>, <a href="http://steamcommunity.com/id/dendodge" title="Steam Community profile" class="url ext">playing games</a>, and trying to teach himself to do cool things with <abbr class="abbr" title="PHP Hypertext Preprocessor - recursive acronyms are awesome">PHP</abbr> (of which this website was a result).</p>
		<p>He has also worked as a freelance journalist, writing a number of articles for <a href="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki/User:Dendodge" class="url ext" title="Wikinews userpage">Wikinews</a> and the now-defunt OpenGlobe, of which he was a project manager. His work on the projects was varied, ranging from short synthesis pieces to in-depth investigative reporting on science &amp; technology topics, and also included administrative work.</p>
		<p>Other work includes writing a novel and image &amp; audio restoration, as well as web design; a select <a href="?p=portfolio">portfolio</a> of this and other work is available.</p>
		<p>He speaks English, HTML, CSS, and Wikisyntax fluently, and has a working knowledge of French and PHP, having also dabbled in <a href="http://duolingo.com/#/dendodge" title="Duolingo profile" class="url ext">German</a>, Esperanto, and JavaScript.</p>
</div>